50|$|Upon {{the return}} of the {{coalition}} government formed by the Christian Social Party (CSV) and the Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party (LSAP) {{as a result of the}} legislative elections of 7 June 2009, Jean <b>Asselborn</b> retained the offices of Deputy Prime Minister, Minister of Foreign Affairs on 23 July 2009. In October 2012, at his instigation, Luxembourg was for the first time elected to a non-permanent seat on the United Nations Security Council for 2013 and 2014.|$|E
